I think that the issue is that every time the `change` event gets triggered on a select the `sum` variable is defined and assigned to zero inside the `change` callback function, I&#39;d suggest to move this variable to the outer `GetData` scope:

    function GetData() {
       var sum = 0;
       var s = $(&#39;select&#39;).change(function() {
             s.each(function() {
               sum += Number(this.value) || 0;
             });
             console.log(sum);
           });
      }
Regarding the other question you can add a handler to the `id=sel` select element that will get its value, then add a data attribute (`data-group`) to all option elements with a group id. Inside the handler for `sel` you&#39;ll query all elements with the group value `document.querySelectorAll(&#39;option[data-group=&quot;+ group_id +&quot;]&#39;)` group_id will be set as an option value in `sel` and the hide all elements (`el.style.display = &#39;none&#39;`)

I hope that helps

